- description "Makers Academy is London's leading Web Developer Bootcamp. Learn to code in 12 Weeks by enrolling on one of our programming / web development courses! Learn Ruby, JavaScript and the best software practices."
- @hide_from_google = true
- @hide_nav = true

%section.hero-splash{style: "background-image: url(#{image_path("backgrounds/dan-and-students-overhead-70.jpg")});"}
  .container
    .centered-row
      %h1 Join the PreCourse Beta
      %p Makers Academy is Europe's leading Web Developer bootcamp. We're aiming to launch a new product and need you to test it out!
      %p The information below will tell you what's involved in our PreCourse Beta.

%section
  .container
    .centered-row
      %h2 PreCourse Beta
      %h4.subheader Details
    .three-width-row
      .column
        %h5 Why we're doing this?
        %p We know our interview process is strict. We'd like to spend more time with you before you join the full time course. Ideally you'll be aiming to join Makers Academy as a full time student in February or March 2017
      .column
        %h5 What you'll do
        %p Over 8 weeks, you'll cover the basics of
        %a Github, Command Line and Ruby - all in preparation to start coding with us full time. You'll have full access to all of our PreCourse curriculum materials and work at your own pace.
      .column
        %h5 What we'll do
        %p We'll provide you with a series of instructional emails for you to follow through. Along with our resources, you'll learn how to pair program with other people, solve complex problems and seriously improve your skills as a Junior Developer

%section.backgrounded
  .container
    .centered-row
      %h2 How does it work?
    .three-width-row
      .column
        %h5 Apply
        %p Complete our application form to register your interest. You'll be directed to book a call with one of our team over the next week to secure your space.
      .column
        %h5 Join
        %p Following your phone call, if you're suited to the next start date, you'll be invited to join the first ever PreCourse Beta from Makers Academy. We're limiting the spaces to ensure you get the best experience.
      .column
        %h5 Code
        %p Once launched, you'll be expected to keep up with fortnightly targets on coding challenges. You'll need around 10 - 15 hours per week to complete this course successfully. If you complete the course this will count towards your PreCourse learning for a full time place on either the February or March course.
      .column
        %h5 Equipment
        %p You'll need your own laptop, a good internet connection and a decent set of headphones with a mic. You can do this course on a Mac, Linux or Windows machine.

